UI_visible_response: Vocational Skills Education and Training Centers (VSETCs) are facilities that combine course learning with practical training to improve the trainees' operational skills. These centers aim to provide learners with essential skills that enhance their employability and support their personal development3. However, it is important to note that some VSETCs have been subject to sanctions due to concerns over human rights abuses, including allegations of forced labor and coercive social integration practices2. The concept of VSETCs represents a significant innovation over prior labor reform initiatives but has also raised serious ethical and legal questions1.
